10/11/2004
HELSINKI, Finland -- Bulgarian President Georgi Parvanov kicked off a two-day visit to Finland on Tuesday (9 November), accompanied by a delegation of business community leaders.
Parvanov met with Finnish counterpart Tarja Halonen and Finnish Prime Minister Matti Vanhanen to discuss intensified bilateral co-operation as well as Bulgaria's EU membership bid.
He also extended an official invitation to the Finnish telecom giant Nokia to open a branch in Bulgaria.
In other news, Bulgaria on Wednesday marks the 15th anniversary of the fall of communism.
On 10 November 1989, dictator Todor Zhivkov stepped down as leader of the ruling party.
(Sega - 10/11/04;
BNT - 09/11/04)
